      ]
    }
  ],
  "potential_mitigations": [
    {
      "phase": [
        "Architecture and Design",
        "Operation",
        "Implementation"
      ],
      "description": [
        "When the data is stored or transmitted through untrusted sources that could modify the data, implement integrity checks to detect unauthorized modification, or store/transmit the data in a trusted location that is free from external influence."
      ]
    }
  ],
  "demonstrative_examples": [
    {
      "text": "\n               \u003cIntro_Text\u003eIn the code excerpt below, an array returned by a Java method is modified despite the fact that arrays are mutable.\u003c/Intro_Text\u003e\n               \u003cExample_Code Nature=\"bad\" Language=\"Java\"\u003e\n                  \u003cxhtml:div\u003eString[] colors = car.getAllPossibleColors();\u003cxhtml:br/\u003ecolors[0] = \"Red\";\u003c/xhtml:div\u003e\n               \u003c/Example_Code\u003e\n            "
    }
  ],
